# Reactor Standalone Package Manager

[Reactor](https://github.com/Kartaverse/Reactor-Standalone) is a package manager created by the [We Suck Less Community](https://www.steakunderwater.com/wesuckless/viewforum.php?f=32) for BMD Fusion Studio, Resolve (Free), Resolve Studio, Assimilate Scratch and LiveFX, OpenFX, JangaFX, SideFX Houdini, and LightWave. Reactor streamlines the installation of 3rd party content through the use of "Atom" packages that are synced automatically with a Git repository.


The new [Reactor Standalone](https://github.com/Kartaverse/Reactor-Standalone) beta allows Kartaverse to work with Resolve Free v15 - v20+, Resolve Studio v15 - v20+, and Fusion v9.0.2 to v20+. This dedicated standalone desktop application version of Reactor helps solve the UI manager scripting dependency issue that was present with Resolve Free v19.1 - 20. The Reactor Package Manager has been revamped as a desktop application that works seamlessly on macOS, Windows, and Linux.

## Solving PathMap Issues

If you have a PathMap issue that causes problems with Resolve, the PathMap settings are stored in a Lua Table structure based file format at the following location:

**Windows:**

`%appdata%\Blackmagic Design\DaVinci Resolve\Fusion\Profiles\Default\Fusion.prefs`

**Mac:**

`$HOME/Library/Application Support/Blackmagic Design/DaVinci Resolve/Fusion/Profiles/Default/Fusion.prefs`


**Linux:**

`Profiles:/Default/Fusion.prefs`

Rename the file to "Fusion.prefs.bak" and that setting file will be skipped. A default "Fusion > Fusion Settings" menu set of prefs will be generated on the next Resolve launch.
